Wilton Brands names Jerry Levin CEO


(Crain's) -- Wilton Brands Inc. has given interim CEO Jerry W. Levin the job permanently.
Mr. Levin, who will continue as the Woodridge-based company's chairman, became CEO at the end of October when Richard Conti resigned.
Wilton Brands Inc. sells cake-decorating, bakeware, scrapbooking and Martha Stewart Crafts items.
In mid-October Wilton parent Wilton Holdings Inc. struck a restructuring deal with its largest creditors, TowerBrook Capital Partners L.P. and Deutsche Bank Trust Co. Americas, after they attempted to force Wilton Holdings into bankruptcy over $208 million in unpaid debt. The two creditors became majority owners of Wilton Holdings.
That involuntary bankruptcy petition did not include Wilton Brands.
In a statement, Mr. Levin said: "Since serving as chairman and interim chief executive officer, I have been impressed with Wilton, and its great products, brands and people. I am enthusiastic about the opportunities that exist at Wilton. "


Consumer Products



























